OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,FStormont's Irish language and Ulster-
OL,7,FScots Commissioners appeared before an
OL,8,Fassembly committee on Wednesday for
OL,9,Fthe first time since taking up their
OL,10,Fposts last autumn.
OL,12,FPol Deeds and Lee Reynolds were joined
OL,13,Fby the director of the new Office of
OL,14,FIdentity and Cultural Expression, Dr
OL,15,FKaty Radford.
OL,17,FFunding for the roles was discussed by
OL,18,Fthe Executive Office Committee, but it
OL,19,Fwas comments which were made by Mr
OL,20,FDeeds in a recent interview that faced
OL,21,Fcriticism from some members.
OL,26,@kD@BrwtD@Brw
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,FThe Irish language commissioner
OL,7,Finsisted he was "trying to distance"
OL,8,Fhimself from a group's decision to
OL,9,Fwork towards a united Ireland.
OL,11,FIn February, Conradh na Gaeilge voted
OL,12,Fto amend its constitution to "work
OL,13,Ftowards a united Ireland for the
OL,14,Fbenefit of the Irish language and the
OL,15,FGaeltacht".
OL,26,@kD@BrwoD@QOUoD@dO]tD@^OUwD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,FShortly afterwards, Northern Ireland's
OL,7,FIrish language commissioner, Pol
OL,8,FDeeds, criticised hostility towards
OL,9,FIrish and was quoted as inviting
OL,10,Fpeople to reflect "that every word
OL,11,Fspoken against the Irish language
OL,12,Fcould be seen in one sense as another
OL,13,Fblow struck in the cause of Irish
OL,14,Funification".
OL,26,@kD@BrwoD@_rwrD@SOUvD@LO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,FThe remarks were criticised by some
OL,7,Funionists as straying into
OL,8,Fconstitutional issues and evoking a
OL,9,FTroubles-era phrase attributed to a
OL,10,FSinn Fein official that "every word of
OL,11,FIrish spoken is a bullet fired for
OL,12,FIrish freedom".
OL,14,FOn Wednesday, Mr Deeds said he was
OL,15,F"parodying" the original phrase and
OL,16,F"turning it on its head".
OL,26,@kD@BrwrD@YOUtD@NO]wD@AOUwD@KO]xD@AOUxD@
OL,26,AXO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,FHe told Stormont's Executive Office
OL,7,FCommittee that he had been inviting
OL,8,Fpeople to "reflect on that
OL,9,Fpossibility" as a response to Conradh
OL,10,Fna Gaeilge's decision, which he said
OL,11,Fwas made by young activists who were
OL,12,F"radicalised by ongoing hostility to
OL,13,Fthe Irish language".
OL,15,FMr Deeds previously canvassed on
OL,16,Fbehalf of Sinn Fein but said he had
OL,17,Fleft the party about five years ago.
OL,26,@kD@BrwpD@KOUqD@LO]tD@AOUuD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,FAsked by DUP MLA Philip Brett if he
OL,7,Fbelieved it was his role to give out
OL,8,Fconstitutional advice, the
OL,9,Fcommissioner said it was "absolutely
OL,10,Fnot constitutional advice".
OL,12,F"The advice was for people to reflect
OL,13,Fupon the consequences of their
OL,14,Factions, in terms of the ongoing
OL,15,Fhostility towards the Irish language
OL,16,Fand towards my office."
OL,18,FMr Deeds told the committee his
OL,19,Fresponse was "appropriate" but it had
OL,20,F"snowballed" when "people were
OL,21,Fencouraged to react to reaction".
OL,26,@kD@BrwqD@ZOUrD@ZO]tD@AOUxD@WO]{D@NOU{D@
OL,26,AZO]|D@AOU|D@LO]|D@SOU}D@`O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,FHe said that several unionists had
OL,7,Ftold him what he said was right and
OL,8,Fquestioned whether some of the offence
OL,9,Fexpressed was legitimate.
OL,11,FAsked by Mr Brett why some in the
OL,12,FProtestant, Unionist, and Loyalist
OL,13,Fcommunity were suspicious of Irish,
OL,14,Fthe commissioner said issues around
OL,15,Fidentity and language had previously
OL,16,Fnot been dealt with well and that past
OL,17,Fconflict had been "partly related" to
OL,18,Fidentity and language.
OL,26,@kD@BrwyD@SOUyD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,FAsked how the Conradh na Gaeilge
OL,7,Fdecision would help unionist
OL,8,Funderstanding of the Irish language,
OL,9,FMr Deeds said: "When I gave my
OL,10,Fcomments, I was actually trying to
OL,11,Fdistance myself from their decision."
OL,13,FPressed on whether it was wrong, he
OL,14,Freplied: "I don't want to say too much
OL,15,Fbecause they're a democratic
OL,16,Forganisation."
OL,18,FHowever, he said he had challenged
OL,19,Feveryone at the Conradh na Gaeilge to
OL,20,Fthink about including other cultures
OL,21,Fand identities.
OL,26,@kD@BrwqD@POUsD@eO]vD@JOUxD@NO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,FHe said he asked Lee Reynolds,
OL,7,Fcommissioner for the Ulster Scots and
OL,8,Fthe Ulster British tradition, to
OL,9,Fdisregard an exclusion for his own
OL,10,Foffice from facilitation guidance.
OL,12,FTUV MLA Timothy Gaston also dedicated
OL,13,Fhis committee time to challenging the
OL,14,Fcommissioner's past comments.
OL,16,FMr Gaston accused Mr Deeds of
OL,17,F"continuing in the vein" of his former
OL,18,Fparty, Sinn Fein, and "politicising"
OL,19,Fthe Irish language.
OL,26,@kD@BrwyD@AOUyD@XO]zD@WOUzD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,FHe said the commissioner showed "no
OL,7,Fself awareness" and a lack of
OL,8,Funderstanding of unionist concerns.
OL,10,FMr Deeds said: "I would love to ask
OL,11,Fyou, do you honestly not get the point
OL,12,FI was making?"
OL,14,FThe commissioner accused Mr Gaston of
OL,15,F"attacking" him and "politicising" his
OL,16,Foffice.
OL,26,@kD@BrwnD@aOUoD@OO]rD@POUtD@NO]wD@AOUwD@
OL,26,AKO]wD@UOUwD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44511
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,FThe TUV MLA said: "You've confirmed my
OL,7,Fsuspicion that you have no self
OL,8,Fawareness of how this is seen within
OL,9,Funionism, of how the Irish language
OL,10,Fbeing inflicted on unionist
OL,11,Fcommunities in Belfast, how that
OL,12,Fparody of that 1982 slogan has been
OL,13,Freceived within unionism."
OL,15,FMr Deeds said he did not understand Mr
OL,16,FGaston's interpretation of his wording.
OL,26,@kD@BrwnD@SOUuD@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44512
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,F"There's a clear link between this
OL,7,Fongoing hostility shown towards the
OL,8,FIrish language and to my office, and
OL,9,Fpeople becoming radicalised and pro-
OL,10,FUnited Ireland. It was a very obvious
OL,11,Fpoint."
OL,13,FThe commissioner added that every time
OL,14,Fhe speaks he promotes respect for the
OL,15,FUlster Scots and Ulster British
OL,16,Ftraditions.
OL,18,FHe told Mr Gaston: "Your party leader
OL,19,Fcalled me a bigot a couple of weeks
OL,20,Fago, like it's not in the real world."
OL,26,@kD@BrwnD@AOUsD@GO]zD@TOU|D@fO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G12/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44513
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,FMr Gaston also questioned Mr Deeds on
OL,7,Fhis opinion of loyalist activist Jamie
OL,8,FBryson.
OL,10,FThe commissioner said he did not want
OL,11,Fto apologise for any previous comments
OL,12,Fabout Mr Bryson and expressed a desire
OL,13,Fnot to comment on him.
OL,15,FAsked if he held a personal hostility
OL,16,Fto Mr Bryson, he said: "There's
OL,17,Fclearly a personal hostility coming
OL,18,Ffrom the other direction.
OL,20,F"I don't know the individual, but I
OL,21,Fcan't go too far into those issues."
OL,26,@kD@BrwxD@XOU|D@AOU}D@dO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G13/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44514
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,FMr Deeds told the committee he was
OL,7,F"asked the question" about whether Mr
OL,8,FBryson's challenges to Irish language
OL,9,Fsignage were lawful.
OL,11,FFollowing the session with Mr Deeds,
OL,12,Fthe committee agreed with suggestions
OL,13,Fby Mr Gaston and Mr Brett to seek an
OL,14,Fanswer on whether that question was
OL,15,Flegal advice coming from his own
OL,16,Fbudget or the Executive Office ` and
OL,17,Fon what grounds that query was made.
OL,26,@kD@BrwoD@AOUoD@TO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G14/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44515
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,FThe committee also heard from Mr
OL,7,FReynolds and the director of the
OL,8,FOffice of Identity and Cultural
OL,9,FExpression, Dr Katy Radford.
OL,11,FThey, along with Mr Deeds, expressed
OL,12,Fconcern about budgetary constraints
OL,13,Fimpacting their ability to hold
OL,14,Fevents, do research, and recruit the
OL,15,Fnecessary amount of staff.
OL,26,@kD@Brw
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G15/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44516
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,FMr Reynolds said, under the existing
OL,7,Fbudgetary parameters, one-off set-up
OL,8,Fcosts combined with inflation and
OL,9,Fpublic sector pay rises had placed a
OL,10,F"ball of chain around our ankles"
OL,11,Frather than allowing a "full running
OL,12,Fstart".
OL,14,FOn the work of his office, he said he
OL,15,Fwas examining whether Ulster Scots
OL,16,Ffell under existing equality law
OL,17,Fprotections and whether a legal
OL,18,Fchallenge would be necessary ` adding
OL,19,Fthat he would hope to have an answer
OL,20,Fbefore summer.
OL,26,@kD@BrwrD@AOUrD@aO]sD@XOUtD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G16/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44517
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1773940276
OL,3,CPol Deeds defends comments on language
OL,4,Cand Irish unity as 'parody'
OL,6,FHe later suggested that the World Pipe
OL,7,FBand Championships, normally held in
OL,8,FGlasgow, "might be looking for
OL,9,Fsomewhere to go".
OL,11,FDr Radford told the committee that her
OL,12,Foffice's grant-making function had yet
OL,13,Fto be determined and that Castlereagh
OL,14,FFoundation research body had yet to be
OL,15,Fgiven powers.
OL,17,FCatch up with the latest UTV Live on
